\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"I solved this puzzle properly, by hand! It only took like four hours.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":70,\"offset\":69}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":70,\"offset\":69}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"You know there's a simple algorithm for this puzzle: you just have to construct and solve a 54x54 linear system in ℤ₂! Each cell influences some subset of the other cells (and sets them to 1), so you make a column out of each cell to form a matrix 𝐀, as well as a vector for the solution 𝐛, and then solve 𝐀𝐱 + 𝐛 = 0 in ℤ₂.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":71},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":329,\"offset\":399}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":71},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":329,\"offset\":399}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"More in-depth details below the cut, I'll explain all of that at least \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":401},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":72,\"offset\":472}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"em\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"briefly\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":73,\"offset\":473},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":80,\"offset\":480}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":72,\"offset\":472},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":81,\"offset\":481}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\" for folks who don't know what those terms mean. And you won't see the solution unless you want to, if you want to try this method for yourself.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":81,\"offset\":481},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":225,\"offset\":625}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":401},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":225,\"offset\":625}}}],\"data\":{\"quirksMode\":false},\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":225,\"offset\":625}}}"},{"startIndex":4,"endIndex":41,"ast":"{\"type\":\"root\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"hr\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":4,\"offset\":3}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"The first part: we want to model toggling things on and off so we can handle the lights here.\\nLuckily, mathematicians have our back, the set of numbers ℤ₂ represents that well.\\nIn it, there are only two numbers, 0 and 1, and addition works the same as usual except that 1 + 1 = 0 — so adding 1 to a number toggles it on and off.\\nMultiplying is completely normal.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5},\"end\":{\"line\":6,\"column\":34,\"offset\":367}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5},\"end\":{\"line\":6,\"column\":34,\"offset\":367}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Next, we need a bunch of equations to figure out whether each square is toggled.\\nWe give each square a name so we can write about their relations:\\nLet's say:\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":8,\"column\":1,\"offset\":369},\"end\":{\"line\":10,\"column\":11,\"offset\":526}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":8,\"column\":1,\"offset\":369},\"end\":{\"line\":10,\"column\":11,\"offset\":526}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"ul\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"li\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"square 𝑥₀ is toggled by squares 𝑥₀, 𝑥₁, 𝑥₅, and 𝑥₈\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":12,\"column\":3,\"offset\":530},\"end\":{\"line\":12,\"column\":58,\"offset\":585}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":12,\"column\":1,\"offset\":528},\"end\":{\"line\":12,\"column\":58,\"offset\":585}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"li\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"it's initially on in the puzzle\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":3,\"offset\":588},\"end\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":34,\"offset\":619}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":1,\"offset\":586},\"end\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":34,\"offset\":619}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"li\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"we want to turn it off (because it's \\\"Lights Out\\\")\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":14,\"column\":3,\"offset\":622},\"end\":{\"line\":14,\"column\":53,\"offset\":672}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":14,\"column\":1,\"offset\":620},\"end\":{\"line\":14,\"column\":53,\"offset\":672}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":12,\"column\":1,\"offset\":528},\"end\":{\"line\":14,\"column\":53,\"offset\":672}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"We can write that equation as: 𝑥₀ + 𝑥₁ + 𝑥₅ + 𝑥₈ + 1 = 0.\\nConveniently, we can add 1 to both sides of this equation, and get 𝑥₀ + 𝑥₁ + 𝑥₅ + 𝑥₈ = 1, which is slightly nicer to work with later.\\nWe can make one equation like this for each cell in the grid, and then solve them all simultaneously.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":16,\"column\":1,\"offset\":674},\"end\":{\"line\":18,\"column\":102,\"offset\":975}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":16,\"column\":1,\"offset\":674},\"end\":{\"line\":18,\"column\":102,\"offset\":975}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Let's find an actual one of these equations, looking at the very first cell:\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":20,\"column\":1,\"offset\":977},\"end\":{\"line\":20,\"column\":77,\"offset\":1053}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":20,\"column\":1,\"offset\":977},\"end\":{\"line\":20,\"column\":77,\"offset\":1053}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"pre\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"100000\\n010000\\n000000\\n000000\\n000000\\n000000\\n000000\\n000000\\n000000\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":21,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1054},\"end\":{\"line\":31,\"column\":4,\"offset\":1124}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":21,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1054},\"end\":{\"line\":31,\"column\":4,\"offset\":1124}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"We can unwrap this into a straight line that represents all of the cells it impacts:\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":32,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1125},\"end\":{\"line\":32,\"column\":85,\"offset\":1209}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":32,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1125},\"end\":{\"line\":32,\"column\":85,\"offset\":1209}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"pre\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"100000010000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":33,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1210},\"end\":{\"line\":35,\"column\":4,\"offset\":1272}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":33,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1210},\"end\":{\"line\":35,\"column\":4,\"offset\":1272}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"This isn't quite what we want for making our equations, instead of telling us what cells impact the first cell, this tells us which cells the first cell impacts.\\nHowever, we can find this information pretty easily!\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":36,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1273},\"end\":{\"line\":37,\"column\":53,\"offset\":1487}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":36,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1273},\"end\":{\"line\":37,\"column\":53,\"offset\":1487}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"If we do this process for each cell on the board, we get 54 (6x9) of these 54-entry vectors.\\nIf we use these as \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":39,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1489},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":20,\"offset\":1601}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"em\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"columns\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":21,\"offset\":1602},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":28,\"offset\":1609}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":20,\"offset\":1601},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":29,\"offset\":1610}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\" of a matrix, we end up with columns that represent all of the cells that a given cell impacts, and the rows representing all of the cells that impacts \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":29,\"offset\":1610},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":181,\"offset\":1762}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"em\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"that cell\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":182,\"offset\":1763},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":191,\"offset\":1772}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":181,\"offset\":1762},\"end\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":192,\"offset\":1773}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\".\\nWe do the same unwrapping for the initial state of the board, and set that column next to our matrix, to give us an \\\"augmented matrix\\\" for solving the system.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":40,\"column\":192,\"offset\":1773},\"end\":{\"line\":41,\"column\":159,\"offset\":1933}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":39,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1489},\"end\":{\"line\":41,\"column\":159,\"offset\":1933}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"If we look at the first row of our matrix, we've got:\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":43,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1935},\"end\":{\"line\":43,\"column\":54,\"offset\":1988}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":43,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1935},\"end\":{\"line\":43,\"column\":54,\"offset\":1988}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"pre\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"110000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":44,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1989},\"end\":{\"line\":46,\"column\":4,\"offset\":2053}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":44,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1989},\"end\":{\"line\":46,\"column\":4,\"offset\":2053}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Just to make it clear on last time, this tells us all the cells that toggle the first cell 𝑥₀.\\nTurning this back into an equation, we get: 𝑥₀ + 𝑥₁ + 𝑥₆ = 1.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":47,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2054},\"end\":{\"line\":48,\"column\":65,\"offset\":2214}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":47,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2054},\"end\":{\"line\":48,\"column\":65,\"offset\":2214}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"But we're going to want to work directly with the matrix, since it's much easier to solve as a matrix than as a bunch of separate equations.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":50,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2216},\"end\":{\"line\":50,\"column\":141,\"offset\":2356}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":50,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2216},\"end\":{\"line\":50,\"column\":141,\"offset\":2356}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"details\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":52,\"column\":10,\"offset\":2367},\"end\":{\"line\":53,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2368}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"summary\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"The full linear system for this puzzle\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":53,\"column\":10,\"offset\":2377},\"end\":{\"line\":53,\"column\":48,\"offset\":2415}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":53,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2368},\"end\":{\"line\":53,\"column\":58,\"offset\":2425}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"pre\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"code\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"110000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n011000011000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n011000000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n000100000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|0\\n000010000010000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|0\\n000011000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n010000100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n100000110000110000000000000000000000000000000000000000|1\\n001000011000000100000000