000000000000000000010000100000010000|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000101000010000001000|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000011000001000011100|1\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000001110000100001100|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000010000011000010|1\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000011000001000010|1\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000010000100000|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000011000011000|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001000|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000100001100|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000010000111|0\\n000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000011000001|1\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":55,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2427},\"end\":{\"line\":110,\"column\":4,\"offset\":5512}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":55,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2427},\"end\":{\"line\":110,\"column\":4,\"offset\":5512}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":52,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2358},\"end\":{\"line\":112,\"column\":11,\"offset\":5524}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"This big matrix represents the vector equation 𝐜₀𝑥₀ + 𝐜₁𝑥₁ + … + 𝐜₅₃𝑥₅₃ = 𝐛, which you can think of as either a bunch of equations, one for each cell, or one equation acting on the whole board.\\nIt says \\\"𝑥₀ decides if you toggle cells 𝐜₀, 𝑥₁ decides if you toggle the cells 𝐜₁, and so on, and after all the toggling, we want to toggle exactly the cells in the initial board 𝐛.\\\"\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":114,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5526},\"end\":{\"line\":115,\"column\":188,\"offset\":5914}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":114,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5526},\"end\":{\"line\":115,\"column\":188,\"offset\":5914}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"You can solve this with \",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5916},\"end\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":25,\"offset\":5940}}},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"a\",\"properties\":{\"href\":\"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FGaussian_elimination\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Gaussian elimination\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":26,\"offset\":5941},\"end\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":46,\"offset\":5961}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":25,\"offset\":5940},\"end\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":99,\"offset\":6014}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\", which is luckily much easier in ℤ₂ since you only have to toggle between 0 and 1 instead of doing full addition.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":99,\"offset\":6014},\"end\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":213,\"offset\":6128}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":1,\"offset\":5916},\"end\":{\"line\":117,\"column\":213,\"offset\":6128}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"ul\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"li\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"First, try to get it into row-echelon form, which means you need to try to make the lower left triangle of the matrix all zeroes. (If you manage it, it will automatically be in reduced form since there are no numbers besides 0 and 1).\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":119,\"column\":3,\"offset\":6132},\"end\":{\"line\":119,\"column\":237,\"offset\":6366}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":119,\"column\":1,\"offset\":6130},\"end\":{\"line\":119,\"column\":237,\"offset\":6366}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"li\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"In broad terms, you want to add the rows with a leading number along the diagonal to any rows be