<!-- --><p>You can solve this with <!-- --><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaussian_elimination" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Gaussian elimination<!-- --></a>, which is luckily much easier in ℤ₂ since you only have to toggle between 0 and 1 instead of doing full addition.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><ul>
<!-- --><li>First, try to get it into row-echelon form, which means you need to try to make the lower left triangle of the matrix all zeroes. (If you manage it, it will automatically be in reduced form since there are no numbers besides 0 and 1).<!-- --></li>
